  "prompt": "What is a store credit?",
  "response": "Store credit is a form of credit issued by a retailer that allows customers to make purchases without using cash or credit cards. It is typically provided when a customer returns an item, exchanges a product, or receives a reward or promotional offer. Store credit is usually non-transferable and can only be used at the issuing retailer. The amount of store credit is usually equivalent to the value of the returned item or the amount rewarded, and customers can use it for future purchases until the balance is depleted. Some retailers may impose expiration dates or specific conditions on the use of store credit.",
